result.name: Taco Chaca

reviews.text:
I used to be one of the biggest fans of Taco Chaca until my most recent experience. 

I went to the restaurant and was served chilli cheese fries which were cold. When I raised it to a lady who presumably looked like the manager, she mentioned that it was cooked yesterday and that’s why its cold. 

When I complained about being served food cooked yesterday, the lady said I should have asked before ordering. 

Apart from the fact that food was not up to standards, the sheer arrogance of the manager is startling. Instead of being polite, she was shouting and calling on her staff to rally behind her. 

Taco Chaca, unfortunately for you, you’ve lost a customer and probably earned some well-deserved bad word of mouth publicity.

Edit: I’m from America and I’ve never had Mexican food this bad. Just because it’s Cali mex food doesn’t mean it has to be devoid of flavor and mostly bland mushy rice. Maybe you can improve your product if you want good reviews. 

Incredibly sad portions. The burrito I got was 98% flavorless, bland rice and 2% low quality meat. Everything here is greasy too. Not Mexican food at all.
Great place. Fantastic tacos and service.
Best Mexican in Hong Kong hands down! Must try their ox tongue and fish tacos, all their burritos are excellent

Reasonably priced tacos but they're a bit small! We ended up order three orders of tacos, one order of quesadilla and fries for a group of three! Everything was freshly made and really tasty! Hands down, best tacos in the area :) Will come back next time!
